Statement of Qualifications

Senior Transportation Planner (Temporary Assignment)

Huiyu Lin

1. Education and Experience in Transportation Policy and Planning

I hold a Ph.D. in Geography from Kent State University and a Master of Arts in Geography from SUNY Binghamton, with academic training in transportation planning, Geographic Information Systems (GIS), spatial analysis, and quantitative modeling. My education provided a strong foundation in applying data-driven analysis to transportation planning and policy development.

As a Sustainability Transportation Analyst with Caltrans’ Director’s Office of Sustainability, I independently develop analytical methodologies and decision-support frameworks that support statewide transportation planning, sustainability, equity, safety, and Vehicle Miles Traveled (VMT) reduction initiatives.

I currently lead the technical development of a statewide Speed Performance research initiative by creating analytical methodologies to identify excessive speeding on the State Highway System and support future speed abatement planning, aligned with the Caltrans Strategic Management Plan. I also developed the analytical methodology and authored the technical documentation for the Corridor Prioritization Tool, a standardized decision-support framework that supports Caltrans’ Corridor Tiering Process by helping Districts prioritize multimodal corridors and determine appropriate planning tiers using data-driven performance measures in alignment with CAPTI.

I regularly collaborate with multiple Caltrans divisions and offices to support implementation of the Transportation Equity Index (EQI) across transportation planning processes. I have designed and developed analytical use cases that help implement CalSTA’s direction to integrate equity into transportation planning and maintenance prioritization, advancing the Secretary’s vision for a more equitable transportation system in California.

These experiences have strengthened my ability to translate transportation policy into practical analytical methodologies that support statewide planning and data-driven decision-making.

