2. Education and Experience with Data Analysis in the Transportation Field, Including GIS and Statistical Software

I have extensive experience applying GIS, programming, and quantitative analysis to transportation planning using ArcGIS Pro, R, Python, SQL, Tableau, StreetLight, and Replica.

At Caltrans, I independently develop analytical workflows that transform complex datasets into repeatable methodologies and practical planning tools. My work includes developing GIS workflows, automating analyses in R, creating performance metrics, integrating multiple statewide datasets, and preparing maps, dashboards, and technical reports for planners and decision-makers.

I developed a GIS and R workflow integrating Customer Service Request (CSR) data, the Transportation Equity Index (EQI), demographic information, and operational performance measures to conduct statewide spatial and temporal analyses. The results identify patterns in maintenance response and provide data-driven evidence to support equity-informed maintenance prioritization.

As part of the statewide Speed Performance initiative, I am developing analytical methods and performance metrics to identify excessive speeding using NPMRDS traffic performance data. I also conduct before-and-after traffic volume analyses using StreetLight and Replica to evaluate transportation project performance and support rural VMT reduction initiatives.

My technical experience enables me to transform transportation data into decision-support tools that improve planning, investment prioritization, and program implementation across Caltrans.

